<HEADLINE>
GIO TO CHAMPION PUBLISHING INDUSTRY PROMOTION LEGISLATION
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Feb. 1 (CNA) 02/01/07  22:56:34 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The Government Information Office (GIO) will champion the
legislation of a law to facilitate reinvigoration of the
publishing industry and music industry, GIO Minister Cheng Wen-
tsan said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Cheng said the bill would create mechanisms to encourage print,
music and digital publishers to help promote Taiwan's publishing
industry and cultural development.
</P>
<P>
The law's aim is to offer institutional protection and support to
diversified and disadvantaged publishing business, including
small or local newspapers, so that different voices might be
heard by the public, according to Cheng.
</P>
<P>
Cheng said that in addition to advancing the promotion law, the
GIO will also work on amendments to the Radio and Television Act
and Motion Picture Act to enhance Taiwan's culture industries.
</P>
